      "content": "i mean i know what they TELL us, but that's the point. if you look at the packet headers, it's not going to standard telemetry sinks. it's hitting these weirdly obfuscated endpoints that don't match any known service logs. it feels less like error reporting and more like they're trying to map out the user's entire cognitive environment or something. like, why would a system update need to keep polling low-level kernel states so aggressively? doesn't that seem way beyond just \"fixing bugs\"?",
